<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-21T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-21T06:00:00-05:00" n="378" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2817</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-21T13:00:00+02:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1916, 1 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 22, 12
                                    noon</hi>.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4249. <persName corresp="#p_BE1">Bassermann</persName>, member of
                                Reichstag and leader of National Liberal Party, made a speech
                                yesterday in which he demanded the employment of all methods of
                                warfare. This is very significant, as before settlement of submarine
                                controversy in May last, <persName corresp="#p_BE1">Bassermann</persName> supported the Chancellor’s policy.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>